Model Training

#subset the candidates who started the program before 2017
Candidate_1516_C2 <- subset.data.frame(CPAJourney, C2_DateCode < 170 & C2_DateCode > C1_DateCode)

Candidate_1516_C2 <- subset(Candidate_1516_C2, !is.na(Candidate_1516_C2$C2_DateCode)) #create C2's qualified candidate set in 2015 and 2016; remove NA in C2_DateCode

#check that retakers are eliminated
Candidate_1516_C2 <- Candidate_1516_C2[!duplicated(Candidate_1516_C2$ID), ]  #1537

#Calculate the Spell between C2_DateCode and C1_DateCode
Candidate_1516_C2$SemestersBetween <- ((Candidate_1516_C2$C2_DateCode) - (Candidate_1516_C2$C1_DateCode))/2.5

#Create a registration indicator for C2 enrollment
Candidate_1516_C2$NextRegStatus_Binary <-ifelse(is.na(Candidate_1516_C2$C2_DateCode),0,1)
   
#Transform the data to long format. For detailed information on the long format, please refer to: https://www.theanalysisfactor.com/wide-and-long-data/ 
Candidate_1516_C2 <-  dataLong(dataSet = Candidate_1516_C2, timeColumn = "SemestersBetween", censColumn = "NextRegStatus_Binary")    

Candidate_1516_C2$timeInt_Num <-  as.numeric(Candidate_1516_C2$timeInt)
Candidate_1516_C2$LegacyPath <-  as.factor(Candidate_1516_C2$LegacyPath)

#Update the value of "Semester" to reflect the corresponding time of each observation interval.
Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong <- (2.5*((Candidate_1516_C2$timeInt_Num)-1) + Candidate_1516_C2$C1_DateCode)
Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong <- Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong %% 10
Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong [ Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong == 0 ]  <- "Spring"
Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong [ Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong == 2.5] <- "Summer"
Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong [ Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong == 5]   <- "Fall"
Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong [ Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong == 7.5] <- "Winter"
Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong <-  as.factor(Candidate_1516_C2$Semester_DataLong)

#Fit the maximal C2 model with all availiable variables
C2MaximalModelFit <- glm(formula = y ~ timeInt
                        + ExamLocation
                        + BusinessProvince
                        + PrereqGPA
                        + Employer_Cat
                        + LegacyPath
                        + Level
                        + FieldofStudy
                        + Major
                        + ExperienceRoute
                        + Role
                        + Gender
                        + Age
                        + Semester_DataLong
                        , data = Candidate_1516_C2, family = binomial())
#Examine the significance of the variables 
Anova(C2MaximalModelFit, type = "II", test = "Wald" )

#Remove the insignificant variables one by one starting from the variables with largest P-Value (this method is Backward Stepwise Regression)
C2ModelFit_Best <- glm(formula = y ~ timeInt
                        #+ExamLocation
                        #+BusinessProvince
                        + PrereqGPA
                        #+ Employer_Cat
                        + LegacyPath
                        #+Level
                        #+FieldofStudy
                        #+Major
                        #+ExperienceRoute
                        #+Role
                        #+Gender
                        #+Age
                        + Semester_DataLong
                       , data = Candidate_1516_C2, family = binomial())
#Ensure the significance of the all variables in the best model
Anova(C2ModelFit_Best, type = "II", test = "Wald" )

Generate Effect Plots

As in the regression, we can plot effect sizes, which shows how each predictor affects the predicted probability, holding other predictors at a constant value.

#Create effect plot of variables in the best C2 model 
plot(effect("timeInt",C2ModelFit_Best), type = "response")

plot(effect("PrereqGPA",C2ModelFit_Best), type = "response")

plot(effect("Semester_DataLong",C2ModelFit_Best), type = "response")

plot(effect("LegacyPath",C2ModelFit_Best), type = "response")

Enrollment Pattern for Core 2

Prediction on Hold-out Sample

#Predicting 2017 Spring (Datecode 170)
#Select qualified C2 candidates: those who do not take C2 before the prediction time (2017 Spring:170) 
#Ignored the retakers who took C2 before 170 and still eligible for C2 enrollment in 2017 Spring
Candidate_17_C2 <- subset.data.frame(CPAJourney, C2_DateCode >= 170 & C1_DateCode < 170, select = -c(TX_DateCode,FN_DateCode,AS_DateCode,PF_DateCode)) #There are 1087 candidates are eligible for C2

#Compute new spell for the prediction: 170 - C1_DateCode
Candidate_17_C2$SemestersBetween_170 <- ((170 - Candidate_17_C2$C1_DateCode)/2.5)


#Create Semester based on the C1_DateCode
Candidate_17_C2$Semester <- Candidate_17_C2$C1_DateCode %% 10
Candidate_17_C2$Semester[ Candidate_17_C2$Semester == 0 ] <- "Spring"
Candidate_17_C2$Semester[ Candidate_17_C2$Semester == 2.5] <- "Summer"
Candidate_17_C2$Semester[ Candidate_17_C2$Semester == 5] <- "Fall"
Candidate_17_C2$Semester[ Candidate_17_C2$Semester == 7.5] <- "Winter"


#Create dummy variables for categorical variables
Candidate_17_C2 <- dummy_cols(Candidate_17_C2, select_columns = c("Semester"), remove_first_dummy = FALSE )
Candidate_17_C2 <- dummy_cols(Candidate_17_C2, select_columns = c("LegacyPath"), remove_first_dummy = FALSE )
Candidate_17_C2 <- dummy_cols(Candidate_17_C2, select_columns = c("SemestersBetween_170" ), remove_first_dummy = TRUE)
#Change name of dummy 
names(Candidate_17_C2)[names(Candidate_17_C2) == 'Semester_Fall'] <- 'Semester_Summer'
Candidate_17_C2$'Semester_Summer' <- ifelse(Candidate_17_C2$Semester == 'Summer',1 ,0)


#Calculate the propensity 
Candidate_17_C2$Predict <- (exp(1.003065 + 0.012823*Candidate_17_C2$PrereqGPA 
                              + 0.40063805*Candidate_17_C2$SemestersBetween_170_2 
                              - 0.632903*Candidate_17_C2$SemestersBetween_170_4 
                              - 0.0949697*Candidate_17_C2$SemestersBetween_170_5 
                              + 2.457078*Candidate_17_C2$LegacyPath_CGA 
                              + 1.024984*Candidate_17_C2$LegacyPath_CMA
                              + 1.556292*Candidate_17_C2$LegacyPath_NEW
                              - 3.400303*Candidate_17_C2$Semester_Spring
                              - 2.000087*Candidate_17_C2$Semester_Summer
                              - 2.21735*Candidate_17_C2$Semester_Winter
                              )
                /(1+ exp(1.003065 + 0.012823*Candidate_17_C2$PrereqGPA 
                              + 0.40063805*Candidate_17_C2$SemestersBetween_170_2 
                              - 0.632903*Candidate_17_C2$SemestersBetween_170_4 
                              - 0.0949697*Candidate_17_C2$SemestersBetween_170_5 
                              + 2.457078*Candidate_17_C2$LegacyPath_CGA 
                              + 1.024984*Candidate_17_C2$LegacyPath_CMA
                              + 1.556292*Candidate_17_C2$LegacyPath_NEW
                              - 3.400303*Candidate_17_C2$Semester_Spring
                              - 2.000087*Candidate_17_C2$Semester_Summer
                              - 2.21735*Candidate_17_C2$Semester_Winter
                         )))
#Simulation and total the number of prediction
Candidate_17_C2$Sim <- rbinom(1087, 1, Candidate_17_C2$Predict)
sum(Candidate_17_C2$Sim)
## [1] 962
#Number of the candidates indeed enrolled in Spring 2017
Candidate_17_C2$Observed_Binary <-ifelse(Candidate_17_C2$C2_DateCode == 170, 1, 0)  
sum(Candidate_17_C2$Observed_Binary)
## [1] 954
#Number of prediction that is same as oberservated value
Candidate_17_C2$Hit <- ifelse(Candidate_17_C2$Observed_Binary == Candidate_17_C2$Sim, 1, 0)

#Calculate the accuracy of the prediction (Note: there will be variance due to the randomness of each run of simulation)
sum(Candidate_17_C2$Hit)/1087*100
## [1] 80.68077
